LEO ARMOR

The Leo Armor is a powerful and majestic armor worn by the Leo Gold Saint in the Saint Seiya anime and manga series. It is one of the twelve Zodiac armors, each representing a constellation.

This LORA captures the Armor of Leo, ignoring the character, trying to be flexible to be worn by males or females. is based on SD1.5 , and works with Anime models but was not intended for that. I will train another one based on Anime models later on.

items.name: Edward Elric (Fullmetal Alchemist)
items.description:
Lora model of Edward Elric from Fullmetal Alchemist. All previews were done with weight 0.9. I started using Additional Networks extension so lora is no longer in the prompt.

This one was so frustrating to do because the first version of model I trained worked really well, except for automail which kept appearing on both arms. So I kep redoing it and in the end it's still like that -_-

The prompt for basic look is edward elric, red coat, hood, boots, white gloves, black pants, belt, black jacket, black shirt, braided ponytail.

Tips and tricks:

  • Removing red coat, hood from prompt works very well.

  • You can use just ponytail instead of braided ponytail, result will be different.

  • If you'll have boots in prompt and no pose mentioned he will most likely be crouching since it's very common pose in training set.

  • The tag for automail is prosthetic arm, but like mentioned you will most likely end with two of them a lot. Lowering weight of it below standard 1.0 helps a bit.

  • Use electricity for the alchemy effect.

  • own hands together pose works quite well.

  • The model doesn't know Edward have automail leg.

items.description:
- Again messing with my workflow, I got an interesting result, this time Yotsugi Ononoki! And with this, my three best girls of Monogatari collection as LoRA models is done! In the future I will update them all and make an 3in1 collection, but this doesn't mean it's over, there's many more of Monogatari that I want to make! The model was trained using 75 images. It's tricky to get her hat and V posing to look right, so as normal patience, prompting and searching seeds until it looks nice. The base model for training was AnyLora, you should test it in different models and choose one you find better. Needs a decent prompt.
- Don't forget to favorite to get notified when there is any update.
- Recommended weight 0.7 to 0.9, and HiResFix. Also fix the LoRA file name if you use my prompt.
- Note that I use XFORMERS and Negative TI's, so if you're trying to recreate my example images, it will be different.
- If you use it and post on Twitter or Pixiv, please tag me or in the comments, I want to see your creations! You all are free to comment, I appreciate any advice to make it better. Thanks!

items.name: Violet Evergarden LoRA
items.description:
She could write a letter for you, too!

General Info

This LoRA has been trained using the Anything v4.5 model. It does a good job at generating characters, that closely resemble Violet Evergarden. I am aware that there is already a Violet Evergarden LoRA, but it seems it focuses on full body shots and here i was trying to focus on more close up pictures. You may get really good results with a decent prompt!

Usage

The model has been trained using Kohya so you probably want to use it in the same way as you use other Kohya models. If you are Using A1111's Webui you want to move the file into the models>Lora directory. It is very important to use the relevant trigger word so that you can get results that look close to mine or even better. I advise using a weight of 0.6-1.0 but you might even be able to go lower in some cases.

Recommended keywords are any size breasts (big/huge/gigantic), "covered nipples", "muscular female", "bodycon", "skindentation". Basically anything that has something to do with tight clothing, muscles and breasts. Horns, pointy ears, animal ears, tails and other animal girl tags work well too. "Simple background" can also improve output.

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!
Like my LoRAs and want more? Please consider a small tip towards my electricity bill and further training >.<

Misc
512 resolution trained on NAI without noise offset option for best LoRA compatibility.

You can now get all my LoRAs in one single package if you subscribe to my Patreon (including those not on CivitAI):

The Complete Catalog Download | Patreon

You can use this model on SeaArt here.

Mistoon_Anime is my blend of SD models that tries to achieve a more "cartoony" anime style with thick borders and brighter colors. The aim of this model is not to mimic a particular style, but to achieve an aestethic I like.

This merge has been created using a lot of different models. In the start I've used popular models (and also nieche ones), but now I'm mostly using my custom LoRAs to finetune the model in the way I like.

This model is oriented towards creating girls portraits, but the V2 is also capable of creating male characters in a convincing way.

If you plan to do some inpainting there is also an inpainting version available for you to download.

There are other 4 variants of this model available, check out my profile:

The idea behind Mistoon_Anime is to achieve the modern anime style while keeping it as colorful as possible. A lot of checkpoints available now are mostly based on anime illustrations oriented towards 2.5, but I prefer the bright 2d anime aesthetic.

It creates realistic and expressive characters with a "cartoony" twist. Unlike other anime models that tend to have muted or dark colors, Mistoon_Anime uses bright and vibrant colors to make the characters stand out.

This model can easily do both SFW and NSFW stuff (V1 has a bias towards NSFW keep that in mind).

The v1 version is the original Mistoon_Anime that a lot of you already know. It's bright, cartoony and likes tight clothes 😂. If you've never used the original version I highly recommend to check out the gallery and see if it is for you. If you want to use the V1 you'll need a VAE, I highly suggest you to use this one.

If you want a more traditional anime style, you'll probably want the newest version.

For those who have already used my model, the newest version:

  • Is WAY better at producing images depicting males

  • Has lower distortion at lower resolutions

  • Is way more detailed

  • Has better backgrounds consistency

  • Eyes are more detailed and consistent

  • Is incredibly detailed when working with close-ups or upper body portrait

  • Is better with NSFW than the previous version

  • Works better with CLIP skip set to 2

  • Has already a VAE embedded.

In the past few months I've had a lot of people asking me why their pictures are not as detailed or clean as mine. I've written a few articles about SD, but if you want to learn my exact workflow I highly recommend you to check out my latest one: My Workflow

If you want to test this (or other models), I have made an extension to help me create pictures using a variety of different tags. The previews images have been generated using my custom extension Ranbooru which scrapes tags from random images on gelbooru, safebooru and rule34.

If you want to learn more about my workflow, check out the guides below.

Learn how to create pictures like mine with my step-by-step tutorials:

  • Beginner's Guide

  • Prompting

  • High Resolution

  • Inpainting

  • ControlNet

  • My Workflow

  • Tips and Tricks

I've got a lot of models here on CivitAI (and even more on Patreon), here's some of them:

Initially I used to release every LoRA here on CivitAI, but after a while it became very time-consuming, so I started releasing only my favourite new LoRAs here on CivitAI while still releasing all the models for free on Patreon.

So if you don't want to miss a release be sure to follow me on Patreon (for free you don't need to sub if you don't want to) here:

https://www.patreon.com/Inzaniak

If you want to check out my other models you'll find them here:

Inzaniak Catalog

I've started developing custom models for myself a few months ago just to check out how SD worked, but in the last few months it has become a new hobby I like to practice in my free time. All my checkpoints and LoRAs will always be released for free on Patreon or CivitAI, but if you want to support my work and get early access to all my models feel free to check out my Patreon:

items.name: Female sports - AutoPrompt - Awesome prompt lists
items.description:
Description

Female sport themed prompt lists generated from multiple curated datasets.

Portraits of females in various sporting endeavours, various yoga poses and so on.

Usage

Useful for when you want to create images and later go through and pick out the best creations. These prompts are randomly generated every time I generate new lists.

I use them in conjunction with a stable diffusion image viewer I have written where I view thousands of images I've created to find:

  1. Good prompts that have an art style I like

  2. Good prompts that create really good images

  3. Good compositions

How to use prompt files

Prompts from file or textbox

  1. Open automatic1111 SD / any other SD creation tool with similar prompt file input

  2. Select <Script> --> Prompts from file or textbox

  3. Drop file or copy paste contents in the "List of prompts inputs"

  4. To view information on images you have created you can use "PNG Info" tab in Automatic1111.

sd-dynamic-prompts

Can also be used with sd-dynamic-prompts as wildcard lists. You can place the folder for this wildcard collection inside there so that you e.g. have a folder called FemaleSportsAutoPrompt. Then you can use them in your prompt field like __female_training_scifi_images__. See https://github.com/adieyal/sd-dynamic-prompts for more documentation.

items.description:
The beggining of a great project !

Note : don't generate BELOW the base resolution (768*768)

Providence - Prelude 

  • A precise chosen noise offset setting

  • A large variety of subjects, I took care to to keep the flavour at maximum from genesis seeds feel

  • No baked VAE (works fine without any tbh)

Hyper Realism

For good results please use the forAnalogPortrait negative embedding.

Digital painting

For my digital painting finetune, please use “character portrait” along “digital painting” for enhance the quality

Analog

use the forAnalogPortrait negative embedding aswell.

Troubleshoot :

NansException: A tensor with all NaNs was produced in Unet. This could be either because there's not enough precision to represent the picture, or because your video card does not support half type. Try setting the "Upcast cross attention layer to float32" option in Settings > Stable Diffusion or using the --no-half commandline argument to fix this. Use --disable-nan-check commandline argument to disable this check.

A 2.1 model require either --xformers and / or --no-half start argument from the webui-user.bat

set COMMANDLINE_ARGS= --no-half --xformers

check also if your config file is named correctly alongside the model

Happy tuning !

items.name: 90s Anime Aesthetic
items.description:
You can now get all my LoRAs in one single package if you subscribe to my Patreon (including those not on CivitAI):

The Complete Catalog Download | Patreon

What's this LoRA

This is a 90s anime styled LoRA. It can create images in the 90s aesthetic without changing too much the original style of the model.

The images in the examples are created using only this LoRA and different models (mainly my custom: https://civitai.com/models/24149)

You don't need to specify a word to trigger this LoRA, but using 1990s or 90s helps.

The LoRA works also on NSFW (check last examples).

Flavors

The LoRA is now available in 3 different flavors:

  • Soft: This is the most flexible, but the style is also softer

  • Iron: This is the middle one, flexible with a solid style

  • Steel: This is the least flexible, but it has the most intense effect

If you are new to generative art, I recommend using the Soft or Iron version.

items.name: 80s Fantasy
items.description:
IMPORTANT NOTICE:

Hello everyone! Lately in the comments I have often seen people complaining that my LoRA are similar to each other or are not representative of the style they should represent. My models are not trained on material from other artists, and it is therefore difficult to explain what the actual output should be. Since preparing the material necessary for the publication of a LoRA usually takes me a day's work, I have therefore decided not to post all my LoRAs on CivitAI anymore, but from today I will only post those that I consider interesting enough for the audience of this site. If you are interested in downloading the other LoRA as well, you will find them all for FREE (and they'll always be) on my Patreon page (subscribers will have early access to each of these). Thank you all for your support!

I've started a community on Deviant Art to share images made with my models/LoRAs! Join here if you are interested!

What's this LoRA

This is a 80s fantasy movie based LoRA. It's trained on movie posters, so I advise using (text,title,watermark,signature) in the negative prompt to avoid text. This is an experimental LoRA, so the quality of the output can change a lot based on the weight and the prompt.

All the images in the examples have been created using my custom model (https://civitai.com/models/24149) and this LoRA only. All the examples have been created using the hires-fix or by creating the base 512x768 image, upscaling it to 1.5 and the applying the same prompt again as img2img

As the LoRA is trained on real pictures or drawings, use a config between 0.5-0.7 if you want to keep your original art style.

The LoRA works also on NSFW (check last examples).

Versions

There are now 2 different versions:

  • v1: trained on 80s movie posters scraped from the web

  • v2: trained on the same dataset, but this time cleaned from text and colored borders. The output of this version is cleaner and more defined.
